<title>SOUTH AFRICA: S.African Q1 GDP falls annualised 0.8 pct.</title>
<headline>S.African Q1 GDP falls annualised 0.8 pct.</headline>
<dateline>PRETORIA 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>South African gross domestic product (GDP) fell a seasonally adjusted and annualised 0.8 percent in the first quarter of 1997, the Central Statistical Service said.</p>
<p>It said fourth quarter GDP rose 3.3 percent at market prices, unchanged from the preliminary estimate.</p>
<p>The figures are at constant 1990 market prices.</p>
<p>A Reuters poll of economists forecast a first quarter rise of 2.5 percent.  </p>
<p>Seasonally adjusted and annualised percentage change:</p>
<p>    At market prices:   Q1'97 (prel)   Q4'96 (rev)   Q3'96</p>
<p>     GDP		    -0.8		3.3	     3.2</p>
<p>At factor incomes:</p>
<p>     Total		  -1.1		3.1	     3.3</p>
<p>    Agriculture	  -34.1	     12.6	    59.8</p>
<p>     Mining		 -0.4		1.0	    -7.4</p>
<p>     Manufacturing	 3.6		2.2	    -0.9</p>
<p>     Elect, gas, water   4.3		4.9	     6.6</p>
<p>     Construction	  1.5		1.2	     1.0</p>
<p>     Trade catering     -1.2		2.8	    -0.1</p>
<p>     Transport, comms    0.2		2.4	     3.2</p>
<p>     Finance,real estate 1.8		3.8	     3.9</p>
<p>     Community services  2.0		1.8	     2.0</p>
<p>     Less imputations    2.2		4.9	     3.8</p>
<p>     General government  0.5		2.7	     3.0</p>
<p>     Other		   2.0		1.5	     2.0</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
